  "text": "Previous studies have shown that sequence conservation can improve transcription factor binding site predictions [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . Therefore, we combined standard PWM scanning with a four species conservation filtering to identify potential TFBSs and, on this basis, to infer TF-target gene relations for a comprehensive reference transcriptional network (RTN). With this strategy (see Methods for details), we predicted 4,3*10e7 TFBS which are conserved among these four species (hg19, mm9, canFam2, bosTau4). These predictions are linked to 16,900 unique human gene symbols. 47.3% of all human promoters (35,750 RefSeqannotated human promoter regions) share at least one conserved predicted binding site with the mouse, dog, and cow species. When selecting only the best 1% predictions of each TRANSFAC matrix we found that 15,619 genes (43.7%) share a conserved, high-scoring binding site. Altogether, we ended up with 490,277 TFBS predictions.",
